documentation.value: \brief This function performs initialization of software only units that requires no hardware access. \details This function performs initialization of software only units that requires no hardware access. \pre NIL \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function initializes RFE APB2SPI. \details This function enables the internal SPI path. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function initializes multiple digital IPs. \details This function initializes multiple digital IPs, including NVIC, PIT, SRC (CREG, GPR, CSR), Packer, LPUART, SPI Access (SPI Access control, SPI Module Decoder (+SPI2AHB)), FlexIO, CSI2-Tx, BIST, WDMA, CRC, ERM, EIM, INTM, SWT. Clocking digital IPs( including CGM, CMU, LPMU ) are not initialized in this step, as it will be intialized in step 15. STM is not initialized in this step, as it is not used. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function reads the OTP content and check the OTP CRC. \details This function reads OTP content and check the OTP CRC. After validating the integrity of OTP data, this function marks IC_OTP_CONFIG_OK in FCCU startup status. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function initializes Analog Central Control (ACC) unit (HW SPIM IP). \details The initialization of ACC includes enabling clock for all IPs, performing full reset and functional reset for all IPs, configuration of interrupts towards M7 and clearing scracth pad registers. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function programming trimming values from OTP to all IPs registers ( except for PDC and ADC ) \details This function programming trimming values from OTP to all IPs registers ( except for PDC and ADC ) \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function switched GLDO IP to power on mode. \details This function switches GLDO IP to power on mode. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function switches Gbias IP to power on mode. \details This function switches Gbias IP to power on mode to enable bias current to all IPs. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function checks XOSC status and FCCU reset errors. \details This function checks XOSC status and FCCU reset errors. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function initialize analog IPs registers ( except for ADC ) \details This function initialize analog IPs registers ( except for ADC ) to overwrite wrong register reset values. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function switches analog IPs from power down to standby mode (except for RX ADC, ADPLL and MCGEN). \details This function brings all analog IPs (except for RX ADC, ADPLL and MCGEN) from power down mode to standby mode in a defined sequence. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function switches LLDOPADC to power on mode and initializes PDC and RX ADC. \details This function switches LLDOPADC to power on mode and initializes PDC and RX ADC. ( including release functional and IP reset, enabling clocks ) \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function switches Mcgen IP to power on mode. \details This function switches Mcgen IP to power on mode ( including the initialization of AD PLL ). \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures Clock Generation Module (CGM). \details This function configures Clock Generation Module (CGM) to switch to 640 MHz. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function signals that the SoC side can switch to 640Mhz clock generated by Master Clock. \details This function signals that the SoC side can switch to 640Mhz clock generated by Master Clock. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function calibrates RX ADC. \details This function calibrates RX ADC. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function calibrates ATB ADC. \details This function calibrates ATB ADC. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function marks each startup configuration step as okay in ISM in a defined order. \details This function marks each startup configuration step as okay in ISM in a defined order, then reset all errors and unmask ADPLL loss of lock bit in SPIM. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function checks ErrorN status. \details This function checks ErrorN status. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function performs SW FIT test. \details This function performs SW FIT test. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function performs HW FIT test. \details This function performs HW FIT test. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function issues error reset in FCCU and checks errorN status. \details This function issues error reset in FCCU and checks errorN status. \pre All steps prior to this step in rfeSwInit_initialize should be completed successfully. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function initializes RFE \details This function performs all 23 required steps to initialize RFE to a working mode. All steps in this function are not application dependent. \pre NIL \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true, On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL
